item.title: Walmart - Porter Ranch, CA - Black Friday Video Game Carnage
item.description:
Walmart - Porter Ranch, CA - Black Friday Video Game Carnage
This video was taken at the Walmart in Porter Ranch, CA on November 24th, 2011 during the store's Black Friday sales. What you're seeing is a clip taken of a group of shoppers ripping and tearing at each other and a kiosk to get their hands on discounted Xbox 360 games. During the mayhem, one woman thought she was going to be robbed, so she pulled out her pepper spray and blasted the crowd. From my understanding another girl was shot directly in the face with the spray. You can see the Security guards escorting the girl in a white shirt away from the area at the end of the video. All this for a few video games.... This video was shot by Melissa Sampson. For media inquiries please email me at mattjarbo@gmail.com or message me on twitter at http://twitter.com/mjarbo -- Thank you. UPDATE: I was contacted by KTLA 5 to do an interview about the incident. I posted a video about it in the comment section. Please watch.

item.title: Brian Lee - Boys Don't Cry
item.description:
Brian Lee - Boys Don't Cry
Free mp3's download at http://bit.ly/s8KPn4 Free listen and lyrics from http://brianleemusic.com/moth/ or http://brianleemusic.com/mp3/ Music video produced by Tim Cash from farfromearthfilms Video featuring Todd Hanson from Bend OR This song isn't intended to be political. It's not about being "for or against" homosexuality. It is simply a song based on the experiences of a heterosexual person who discovered that his best friend is gay. I lived in Los Angeles, California from 1992 to 1996. During my brief stay there, I made three close friendships, but Raymond was my best friend. He was very handsome, like a movie star, and was in great physical shape. He was always surrounded by the prettiest girls...a trait that made me jealous at times. Ray was very athletic, and enjoyed playing tennis... so much so that he also gave lessons. We met at L.A. City College during my freshman year. A love of music was one of the things we had in common, and soon we bonded over a mutual admiration of (as unlikely as it seems) Johnny Mathis. We hung out together often, doing all the typical "guy stuff." We went to the movies, sampled different restaurants and bars, and even took the occasional road trip to party in different cities. But during our entire friendship, he always had another group of friends that I would never meet. I never understood this. Then one night, I learned the reason why. It was because of a conversation we once had concerning Gay Rights. It was now 1996, and I was getting ready to move to Seattle, Washington. Ray called to wish me well, but he was upset. When I asked him what was wrong, he brought up the topic of our previous conversation. Then he confessed to me that he was gay. And how much it hurt to hear my opinions. Somehow Ray got the impression after that discussion that I wasn't interested in being his friend. Nothing could be further from the truth. We lost contact once I moved to Seattle. And it always bothered me that I didn't say or do enough to tell him that his being gay never bothered me... and that he was always one of my best friends. Ray... this song is for you. LYRICS: Boys Don't Cry =========== Last time you saw me It was raining all day Unusual for May But so are your ways I saw those tears falling Down from your eyes You couldn't disguise As you turned away Oh what's on your mind Tell me no lies There's no goodbye Without saying why Then with a sigh A revelation unwinds What a surprise Then you told me you were so afraid But the way I feel about you is unswayed Don't you ever forget that Boys don't cry Remember what I told you that Boys don't cry Let me wipe your tears away Boys don't cry I said Please don't forget that (As I 'm trying to hide my tears) Boys don't cry I ask myself then what this world is about So what makes you wrong And what makes it right How cruel has this world been to you I'll never know but this much is true, I'm still your friend Don't you ever forget that Boys don't cry Remember what I told you that Boys don't cry Let me wipe your tears away Boys don't cry I said Please don't forget that (As I 'm trying to hide my tears) Boys don't cry
